WEBVTT

00:09.260 --> 00:11.091
(POLICE DISPATCH CHATTER)

00:14.265 --> 00:16.551
(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING)

00:17.894 --> 00:19.680
(ROOSTER CROWS)

00:20.438 --> 00:21.803
I give up.

00:21.898 --> 00:24.810
What the hell are we doing here
and Why'd you call for a marked unit?

00:24.901 --> 00:27.392
LKA in Percy Mackie's jacket.

00:28.279 --> 00:29.860
Percy is...

00:29.947 --> 00:31.903
Earl Brown's half-brother.

00:32.950 --> 00:36.534
Brown's a secondary suspect
in the Christmas night shooting.

00:36.621 --> 00:39.704
Primary suspect's gun is inadmissible
'cause you and Cappell shit the bed.

00:39.790 --> 00:41.701
I know who Earl Brown is.

00:41.792 --> 00:44.534
Pardon me if his half-brother's name
doesn't ring a bell.

00:44.629 --> 00:46.494
Just do your fuckin' job, Detective.

00:46.589 --> 00:48.045
That's all | ask.

00:48.132 --> 00:49.997
That's not all you ask.

00:51.093 --> 00:53.584
When your attorney friend's husband
offed himself,

00:53.679 --> 00:56.921
you asked me to look the other way
and let her clean out his truck.

00:57.016 --> 00:58.927
You remember that?

00:59.018 --> 01:01.054
From where I'm sitting,
that pretty white shirt of yours

01:01.145 --> 01:03.010
has got a little dirt on it, too.

01:03.773 --> 01:05.684
-Let's go.
-I think I'll post here.

01:07.026 --> 01:08.732
Fine.

01:08.819 --> 01:10.320
Keep an eye on the door.

01:10.404 --> 01:12.520
Put one of those uniforms around back.

01:12.615 --> 01:15.573
-You can do that, can't you?
-We got you, Lieu.

01:15.660 --> 01:17.696
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:26.212 --> 01:27.827
(ROOSTER CROWS)

01:29.840 --> 01:32.126
(MUSIC BLARING)

01:32.218 --> 01:34.425
-Percy Mackie?
-All day.

01:34.845 --> 01:37.928
-Mind if I come in?
-If you had the paper, you could.

01:38.015 --> 01:41.633
-That how you want it to go?
-Suit yourself, big man.

01:42.645 --> 01:44.852
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:51.696 --> 01:54.779
-Who's he?
-Just some boy.

01:54.865 --> 01:57.993
I'm looking to speak
with your brother, Earl Brown.

01:58.077 --> 02:00.284
I ain't seen that fool for weeks.

02:00.371 --> 02:02.862
I don't associate with his kind no more.

02:02.957 --> 02:05.289
-Truth.
-No?

02:06.168 --> 02:07.783
That ain't me no more.

02:08.004 --> 02:09.995
I'm in culinary school.

02:11.882 --> 02:13.338
You, sit down.

02:13.426 --> 02:15.963
-Hey, I said sit!
-(DOOR OPENS)

02:23.936 --> 02:25.676
Oh, fuck.

02:29.900 --> 02:31.231
(DOG BARKING)

02:31.902 --> 02:34.644
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

02:44.123 --> 02:46.239
(CHATTERING)

02:47.084 --> 02:49.541
(MUSIC PLAYING)

04:36.026 --> 04:38.608
-All right. Thanks, man.
-Sure.

04:40.865 --> 04:43.402
(MUSIC PLAYING OVER STEREO)

04:43.492 --> 04:45.198
What the hell is all that?

04:45.286 --> 04:48.995
'58 Mercury Monterey records brochures.

04:49.540 --> 04:52.703
Spring and fall lists, all releases.

05:04.096 --> 05:05.381
What?

05:06.515 --> 05:08.551
The opera's not there.

05:08.851 --> 05:10.261
It's not in the fall releases.

05:10.352 --> 05:13.014
It's not... Fuck, it's not there.

05:13.814 --> 05:16.977
She's been telling you
she doesn't want to fund it, Davis.

05:17.651 --> 05:18.936
Yeah, but I didn't...

05:19.028 --> 05:21.144
I didn't think she'd have the balls
to tell me no.

05:21.238 --> 05:23.229
Not, not for real.

05:23.908 --> 05:27.651
-|t's her money.
-lt's my label, too!

05:27.745 --> 05:30.236
She wouldn't be
in this business except for me.

05:30.331 --> 05:31.992
Fuck!

05:41.258 --> 05:43.749
My man, take solace.

05:46.805 --> 05:48.306
DESIREE: Your company did the painting

05:48.390 --> 05:51.006
and the landscaping on this house, right here.

05:51.101 --> 05:53.387
And then y'all came
and tore the same house down.

05:53.479 --> 05:55.970
Your sign was out front. Saw your trucks, too.

05:56.065 --> 05:58.556
Yes, ma'am. Those were our trucks.

05:58.651 --> 06:00.187
That's all you have to say?

06:00.277 --> 06:01.858
You took money to fix up a house

06:01.946 --> 06:03.402
and money to tear the same house down.

06:03.489 --> 06:06.481
Actually, more than one.
We're contracted with the city.

06:06.784 --> 06:10.618
They paid us to do
remediation and demolition,

06:10.704 --> 06:13.161
sometimes on the same houses.

06:13.249 --> 06:15.456
But the thing is, it was all legal.

06:15.543 --> 06:18.250
-ls it right?
-ROB|NETTE: That's not for me to say, ma'am.

06:18.337 --> 06:19.952
The city asked us to do one thing,

06:20.047 --> 06:21.878
then they turned around
and asked us to do something else.

06:21.966 --> 06:24.457
Well, Mr. Robinette, these photographs
are going up on our website

06:24.552 --> 06:27.794
because what you all are doing to this city
needs to be known.

06:28.889 --> 06:31.471
Can I see you in my office a minute?

06:32.268 --> 06:33.303
Excuse me.

06:42.778 --> 06:44.188
You seen those bitches?

06:44.280 --> 06:46.111
They got shots of the houses, our signs...

06:46.198 --> 06:47.859
I know. We look like shit.

06:47.950 --> 06:49.611
We ain't do nothing
but what they told us to do.

06:49.702 --> 06:50.737
Doesn't matter.

06:50.828 --> 06:52.910
We don't want to be
the poster boys for this stuff

06:52.997 --> 06:55.238
when we finally got better prospects
on the horizon.

06:55.332 --> 06:58.916
The St. Bernard, the Lafitte,
the Jazz Center, all that matters.

06:59.003 --> 07:00.584
This penny-ante NOAH bullshit

07:00.671 --> 07:02.411
is down to the last scraps anyway, right?

07:02.506 --> 07:06.124
-So what we tell them?
-Let me take care of this quick, partner.

07:06.218 --> 07:08.834
-I got a plane to catch.
-Be my guest.

07:14.184 --> 07:15.435
(CHUCKLES)

07:19.857 --> 07:21.848
-Pop.
-You up early.

07:22.526 --> 07:25.063
I thought you musicians slept in.

07:25.904 --> 07:27.405
You up for all this?

07:27.489 --> 07:29.275
It's a one-day pick-up job

07:29.366 --> 07:31.277
before I start my next treatment.

07:31.368 --> 07:34.280
'Cause you know I'm gonna be
flat on my back again

07:34.371 --> 07:36.032
when that chemo kicks in.

07:36.123 --> 07:37.363
(SIGHS)

07:38.292 --> 07:39.998
I'm asking, can you do the work?

07:40.085 --> 07:43.293
I will do it. I'm fine.

07:43.380 --> 07:46.793
-Pop, you ain't got to be hustling like this.
-|dont?

07:52.097 --> 07:54.588
-$20,000?
-So far.

07:54.683 --> 07:57.220
They want you to come with me
to the next planning group meeting.

07:57.311 --> 07:59.893
-They wanna meet you.
-20,000 for what, exactly?

07:59.980 --> 08:02.471
Just what it says, consulting.

08:02.566 --> 08:04.147
Consulting, huh?

08:04.943 --> 08:06.444
What you got going on othenNise?

08:06.528 --> 08:08.109
Playing a tribute tonight for Freddie Hubbard.

08:08.322 --> 08:11.485
-Yeah. I heard Freddie was sick.
-Yeah.

08:11.575 --> 08:12.985
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

08:15.245 --> 08:16.576
Look, can you get that for me?

08:28.842 --> 08:30.457
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

08:30.552 --> 08:32.053
(ENGINE STARTS)

08:32.137 --> 08:34.844
-Please, call me Nelson.
-I remember you.

08:36.266 --> 08:38.177
l have to say,

08:38.268 --> 08:40.350
listening to you ladies talk,

08:40.437 --> 08:42.428
seeing the work you've done...

08:42.564 --> 08:44.555
Now you're about to make
some kind of excuse.

08:44.650 --> 08:46.106
No excuse.

08:46.944 --> 08:50.687
Everything ljust heard you say,
you're absolutely right.

08:51.740 --> 08:53.696
We're out of the NOAH business
as of right now.

08:53.784 --> 08:55.274
My partner and ljust talked it over.

08:55.452 --> 08:58.285
And based on what you're telling us,
we don't want any part of it anymore.

08:58.455 --> 09:01.197
What are you trying to tell us, Mr. Hidalgo?

09:01.291 --> 09:03.907
That you didn't know
you were fixing up houses

09:04.002 --> 09:05.742
and then tearing them down?

09:05.838 --> 09:08.545
I'm telling you that we're contractors
and we did what we were told

09:08.632 --> 09:10.372
on these houses and dozens of others.

09:10.467 --> 09:12.958
We took the work
as it came to us, piecemeal.

09:13.220 --> 09:15.211
We did what the city asked us to do.

09:15.472 --> 09:19.215
And, yeah, we didn't give it much thought
into how it came out

09:19.309 --> 09:21.220
or that some of the houses
we were working on

09:21.311 --> 09:22.972
were some of the same ones
that later came down.

09:23.355 --> 09:26.313
So that's why
we're no longer working for NOAH.

09:26.400 --> 09:30.609
Also, I'd be happy to make
a monetary contribution to your cause.

09:30.696 --> 09:32.402
Money doesn't fix it.

09:32.489 --> 09:36.073
-We're trying to stop these demolitions.
-What do you want?

09:36.160 --> 09:39.027
I want a list of the houses
that are scheduled to be torn down.

09:39.496 --> 09:41.452
l have the addresses
that were assigned to us, sure.

09:41.540 --> 09:44.031
And lwant the names
of all your contacts at NOAH,

09:45.002 --> 09:48.961
whoever's in charge of this fiasco,
whoever you think might have what I need.

09:50.340 --> 09:52.376
You ladies don't play, huh?

09:55.888 --> 09:59.881
Ladies and gentlemen, I regret to inform you

10:00.642 --> 10:03.975
that the opera est fini.

10:04.229 --> 10:07.312
-Say what?
-What do you mean "regret"?

10:09.193 --> 10:13.027
My vision has been strangled in the crib.

10:13.113 --> 10:15.900
Look, the R&B opera dies.

10:17.367 --> 10:19.824
Vulgarians hold the purse strings

10:19.912 --> 10:22.278
and they just can't see it.

10:22.372 --> 10:25.705
Meaning we're not gonna get one thin dime.

10:26.376 --> 10:28.367
What you gonna do,
bury those tracks we cut?

10:28.462 --> 10:29.747
DAVIS: Not exactly. I mean,

10:29.838 --> 10:33.581
although the opera
won't be released in its entirety,

10:33.675 --> 10:38.465
we're gonna pull a few recordings
and put them on a limited CD.

10:38.555 --> 10:40.967
-What songs?
-We're still figuring that out.

10:41.058 --> 10:42.047
Ha.

10:42.142 --> 10:45.430
May I point out
that we still hold the rights to the opera.

10:45.521 --> 10:48.604
You all own the masters and licensing.

10:48.690 --> 10:52.103
So if I run into a backer
up the road, who knows?

10:52.194 --> 10:55.982
-We may yet stage this thing.
-Davis, be real.

10:56.073 --> 10:59.486
-At least we'll get paid for the session.
-(SCOFFS)

10:59.743 --> 11:01.324
Right?

11:01.411 --> 11:04.494
-I told you it was a bad idea.
-You were right.

11:04.581 --> 11:07.744
But I was seriously considering filing
a formal complaint against Officer Wilson.

11:07.835 --> 11:09.871
l have a daughter near your age.

11:09.962 --> 11:11.452
He got close to her.

11:11.588 --> 11:13.965
I thought you said you had people lined up
to talk about the dude.

11:14.049 --> 11:16.415
l'm pulling them out of line.
It's too dangerous.

11:16.510 --> 11:20.719
-But if no one comes fon/vard, then...
-Then no one will be hurt.

11:20.806 --> 11:24.173
Wilson's got no boundaries.
I'm putting this on hold.

11:24.268 --> 11:26.350
-For real?
-TON|: For the time being.

11:26.436 --> 11:27.562
You've been through enough.

11:27.646 --> 11:30.137
Ma'am, you can't imagine
what I've been through.

11:30.232 --> 11:32.518
I told you, it'll take more
than one police officer

11:32.609 --> 11:33.860
with attitude to give me pause.

11:33.944 --> 11:37.903
I appreciate your cooperation, sir,
but I'm gonna let this simmer down.

11:38.115 --> 11:40.026
Wait. Simmer down?

11:40.117 --> 11:41.857
After you done got me fired up twice?

11:41.952 --> 11:45.536
l shipped my daughter out of town.
That's how serious I feel this situation is.

11:45.622 --> 11:48.910
So all that do-the-right-thing bullshit
you was preaching?

11:49.126 --> 11:51.617
-He came after my family.
-We|come to our world.

11:51.712 --> 11:53.953
You're right. I see that now.

11:54.047 --> 11:55.378
So all of what you've done...

11:55.465 --> 11:57.080
It's just gonna get put
in some drawer somewhere?

11:57.175 --> 11:59.461
You're just gonna give up?

11:59.595 --> 12:03.008
-If I can't protect my own...
-How much did you have?

12:04.516 --> 12:07.633
Five brutality complaints,
all with some corroboration.

12:07.811 --> 12:10.723
-All that's not enough?
-To convict a cop in New Orleans?

12:10.814 --> 12:14.102
-Probably not.
-Well, what would be enough?

12:14.860 --> 12:16.725
What takes this motherfucker off the streets?

12:16.820 --> 12:19.402
-An eyewitness.
-An eyewitness?

12:19.489 --> 12:22.481
Someone who was there
when he shoots Abreu or Seals.

12:22.576 --> 12:25.488
Someone who puts the gun in Wilson's hand.

12:26.914 --> 12:29.826
-Okay.
-Okay?

12:31.084 --> 12:34.076
You've been holding out on me, Bernard?

12:34.171 --> 12:35.160
(BELL RINGING)

12:35.255 --> 12:37.462
Hey, Robert, I'll see you tomorrow night.

12:37.549 --> 12:39.210
I'll be there.

12:39.301 --> 12:41.166
-BOY: Hold it, girl.
-G|RL: Stop pushing.

12:42.179 --> 12:44.170
ANTOINE: Hey, Jennifer! Jennifer!

12:45.182 --> 12:46.843
You all right?

12:46.934 --> 12:49.095
-'Cause I didn't hear no fire alarm.
-Gotta go, Mr. Batiste.

12:49.186 --> 12:50.926
Have practice over at St. James.

12:51.021 --> 12:52.727
Playing this Sunday with the Pinettes.

12:52.814 --> 12:54.850
Yeah, all...

12:54.942 --> 12:57.024
Just go, girl.

12:57.110 --> 12:58.566
Hold on, Cherise.

12:59.029 --> 13:01.145
Let me get a word with you.

13:02.824 --> 13:03.950
What'd I do?

13:05.452 --> 13:07.033
You tell me.

13:16.713 --> 13:18.374
(CLEARS THROAT)

13:21.593 --> 13:23.754
Parker. Hey, it's Everett.

13:26.598 --> 13:28.975
I know. I said that I'd try not to call you.

13:29.059 --> 13:32.176
I said I'd try, but we need to talk again, man.

13:33.271 --> 13:35.398
Not on the phone, right.

13:36.525 --> 13:39.187
Tomorrow, sure. When and where?

13:41.238 --> 13:42.569
Okay.

13:43.615 --> 13:47.904
Gene's on Elysian Fields. Yeah, I know it.

13:48.829 --> 13:50.660
Uh-huh.
Pepto-Bismol-looking joint.

13:50.747 --> 13:51.953
Right.

13:52.582 --> 13:55.449
All right, man. Thanks. I'll see you then.

13:58.088 --> 14:01.251
This is the first class of mine
you've made it to all week.

14:01.341 --> 14:03.127
I know. I'm sorry.

14:03.218 --> 14:07.336
I didn't sit you down for an apology.
I'm concerned is all.

14:07.431 --> 14:09.968
I got no big drama to speak of, Mr. Batiste.

14:10.058 --> 14:11.639
You know, just the same old stuff.

14:11.727 --> 14:14.810
Actually, I don't know.
What's going on with you?

14:16.648 --> 14:17.763
Your folks giving you trouble?

14:17.858 --> 14:19.598
If they were around, they might.

14:19.693 --> 14:22.435
-My father been gone.
-And where your mama at?

14:22.529 --> 14:24.736
She got violated on a shoplifting charge.

14:24.823 --> 14:26.859
She's gonna be in lock-up for a little bit.

14:26.950 --> 14:28.815
I've been taking care of my little brother.

14:28.910 --> 14:31.526
-Sounds like a handful.
-He's all boy.

14:31.621 --> 14:35.364
By the time I pack him up, drag him out of
the house, and get him off to school,

14:35.459 --> 14:37.370
I don't feel like doing nothing. I'm tired.

14:37.461 --> 14:40.043
I can see it, but...

14:41.715 --> 14:43.956
I don't want you giving up
on this music thing.

14:44.051 --> 14:45.757
You got potential.

14:45.844 --> 14:47.254
My sisters had potential.

14:47.345 --> 14:50.212
They scored high on their tests,
but they never finished high school.

14:50.307 --> 14:52.673
Coaches told my brother
he had potential, too,

14:52.768 --> 14:55.225
that he could play college ball
if he stuck with it.

14:55.312 --> 14:57.769
Ronald's still working towards his GED.

14:57.856 --> 14:59.972
Everyone I know got potential.

15:00.067 --> 15:02.683
I'm doing what I can now, Mr. Batiste.

15:03.987 --> 15:06.478
(JUKEBOX PLAYING)

15:08.909 --> 15:10.991
Thought I took care of you.

15:11.912 --> 15:15.404
And here you are,
throwing a shadow across my door again.

15:15.499 --> 15:17.239
-More noise complaints.
-What?

15:17.334 --> 15:19.791
Excessive volume of music.

15:19.878 --> 15:22.085
| book live acts in here.

15:22.172 --> 15:25.164
See, you're trying to shut me down,
just like you did King Bolden's.

15:25.258 --> 15:27.544
This town is about music.

15:27.636 --> 15:30.924
Your neighbors say the music
is keeping them up all hours.

15:31.014 --> 15:32.879
And I know exactly who they are, too.

15:32.974 --> 15:36.057
I've been giving them $20 a night.
They came back over here asking for 30.

15:36.144 --> 15:39.181
When I didn't give it up, they called you.
Ain't that right?

15:39.272 --> 15:43.390
I am not privy to your arrangements
with your neighbors.

15:43.485 --> 15:46.067
All I know is I got some more complaints,

15:46.154 --> 15:49.271
and I'm here at the bar now.

16:09.803 --> 16:13.136
-Paid in full, motherfucker.
-For now.

16:18.687 --> 16:20.552
I'm going outside.

16:31.241 --> 16:32.230
(CAR HORN HONKS)

16:33.160 --> 16:35.617
(RADIO PLAYING)

16:46.423 --> 16:49.915
John, John, bring the stick.

17:01.771 --> 17:03.853
You flew in from New York for little ol' me?

17:03.940 --> 17:07.728
Don't flatter yourself.
I've got a couple of prospects l'm chasing.

17:07.819 --> 17:11.403
And that Freddie Hubbard event you're doing,
that could be a target-rich environment.

17:11.489 --> 17:13.866
-Chris, let me get two more Turbodogs.
-You got it.

17:13.950 --> 17:15.656
I wanted to get up with you now.

17:15.744 --> 17:18.486
-Tonight's gonna be crazy.
-You about to fire me or something?

17:18.580 --> 17:19.945
You can't get my hand
out of your pocket that easy.

17:20.040 --> 17:21.029
(LAUGHS)

17:21.583 --> 17:25.701
The thing is we got a European release
coming up for the CD.

17:25.795 --> 17:27.660
And over there, a jazz recording

17:27.756 --> 17:30.748
can actually sell
a few copies if you support it.

17:30.842 --> 17:32.457
I can't go overseas right now.

17:32.719 --> 17:35.461
Del, it's a week, maybe two.

17:36.097 --> 17:38.964
A few key gigs, London, Amsterdam, Paris.

17:39.059 --> 17:41.971
-I told you, my father's sick.
-I know it, and l empathize,

17:42.229 --> 17:45.062
but the label needs help in Europe.

17:45.148 --> 17:48.436
-I can't leave right now.
-Can't or won't?

17:49.861 --> 17:52.068
This is a great city for music,

17:52.155 --> 17:54.271
maybe the best in the world.

17:54.658 --> 17:56.865
But it's a small stage with a low ceiling.

17:56.952 --> 17:59.034
You saying I stay here,
my career's off the rails?

17:59.162 --> 18:02.654
I'm saying you stay in New Orleans,
you're making a choice.

18:05.627 --> 18:08.164
-Damn, you do go on.
-Just doing myjob, Del.

18:13.551 --> 18:14.540
(LOUD CHATTER)

18:14.636 --> 18:16.968
DEREK: Table four. Another Feeny freebie.

18:17.055 --> 18:19.341
Friends of Tim. It's hard to turn the tables

18:19.432 --> 18:20.842
when they show up in clumps like that.

18:20.976 --> 18:23.638
Yeah. They'll be here a few hours.

18:24.187 --> 18:26.428
And it will be comped, of course.

18:26.523 --> 18:29.811
You think they're gonna tip old Derek

18:29.901 --> 18:32.062
when Mr. Tim reaches for the tab?

18:32.153 --> 18:33.484
Hell, no.

18:33.571 --> 18:36.483
A Laurel and Hardy handshake is what I'd get.

18:36.574 --> 18:38.735
A place like this just collects assholes.

18:39.369 --> 18:41.030
Nature of the beast.

18:41.621 --> 18:43.077
Same thing in the theater.

18:43.164 --> 18:44.779
You do something nice, noble-like,

18:44.874 --> 18:48.116
entertain a few folks,
bring a little light into the darkness,

18:48.211 --> 18:51.624
and someone always drops
a big Cleveland steamer

